President Obama has declared a major disaster in the State of New Mexico due to flooding that occurred between August 19-24, 2011. This declaration allows for federal aid to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. Federal funding will be available for emergency work, facility repairs, and hazard mitigation measures on a cost-sharing basis. Mark H. Armstrong has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.